Remote Code Execution via Log Poisoning / PHP Injection
Examining the admin page source shows that each log line ends with a <br> tag, suggesting the logs are being included via PHP include() or readfile(). This is a classic Local File Inclusion (LFI) to Remote Code Execution (RCE) vector.

We can poison the logs by injecting PHP code into a field that gets logged.

Step 1: Change username (via profile edit) to:

php
<?php system($_GET['cmd']); ?>
Step 2: Visit the /admin/ page as Henry. The logs now include the PHP code because the username appears in the log entry.

Step 3: Append ?cmd=<command> to the admin page URL to execute commands.

