Summary of Attack Path
Web App Enumeration → SQL Injection in password change via username field.

Admin Access → Login as Wwbuddy (Henry) with a known password.

Admin Panel LFI → Log poisoning with PHP code in username → RCE as www-data.

Credentials in MySQL Logs → Roberto's SSH password exposed.

SSH as Roberto → Discover Jenny's birthday-based password via file metadata.

Brute-Force SSH → Access as jenny.

SUID Binary → Environment variable injection → root shell.

Lessons Learned
Always sanitize user input in SQL queries.

Avoid logging sensitive data (passwords in MySQL logs).

Do not rely on weak password policies (birthdays).

SUID binaries should never trust environment variables.

